Veteran Nollywood actor, Francis Duru, has celebrated 19 years of marriage with his wife, Adokiye. On his Instagram page on Tuesday, Duru showered praises on the mother of his “three most wonderful kids”, and also professed his “undying love” for her. The Rattlesnake actor, who shared a picture of himself and his wife, wrote in the caption, “Stuck forever, His Design. Blessed with three most wonderful kids, His favour. Sustained, His grace. “Held by the nail for 19 years to an amazing woman. My elegant stallion. I bless the day I found you. You fill the essence fuelled from on high. “Thanks for being you and being there for us. Thanks Dox, no one but you. My undying love I vow forever. We bless God, good people. It’s our wedding anniversary. Your prayers will be cherished most. May the good Lord bless you all abundantly.” Francis, 52, tied the knot with Adokiye in 2003. Their union is blessed with three children. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com